State MSM Profile: New Jersey

Background & Methods

In 2015-2016, researchers at Emory University partnered with colleagues at the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC) to develop methods to estimate the number of men who have sex with men (MSM) residing in each county in the United States. Using population and housing data from the American Community Survey and estimates from two peer-reviewed publications (Oster et al., 2015 & Purcell et al., 2012), they derived an indirect estimate of MSM population sizes that took into account both the urbanicity of the county as well as its density of households with a male householder and a male same-sex partner.

The full methodology is published in the Journal of Medical Internet Research - Public Health and Surveillance:

Grey JA, Bernstein KT, Sullivan PS, Purcell DW, Chesson HW, Gift TL, Rosenberg ES. Estimating the population sizes of men who have sex with men in US states and counties using data from the American Community Survey. JMIR Public Health Surveill 2016;2(1):e14. DOI: 10.2196/publichealth.5365

Overview of MSM in New Jersey

An estimated 132,520 men who have sex with men (MSM) resided in New Jersey in 2013, representing 2.9% of the 4,503,084 MSM in the United States. Of the 3,257,962 adult men of New Jersey, 4.1% had had sex with another man in the past 5 years, which was greater than the overall percentage of adult men in the United States who were MSM (3.9%).

Most MSM in New Jersey resided in fringe counties of large metropolitan areas (59.6%). Including both central and fringe counties, 93.9% resided in a large metropolitan area.


Percentage of MSM by urbanicity, United States and New Jersey, 2013

MSM in New Jersey Counties

Among counties or county-equivalent areas in New Jersey, Hudson County had the largest population of MSM at 18,523, representing 14.0% of all MSM in the state. Hudson County also had the highest percentage of MSM among adult men in New Jersey at 7.4%. This was greater than the percentage for New Jersey as a whole, which was 4.1% of adult men.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.



MSM in New Jersey Metropolitan Statistical Areas

New York-Newark-Jersey City Metropolitan Statistical Area

The New York-Newark-Jersey City MSA overlaps three states: New Jersey, New York and Pennsylvania. The New Jersey portion of the MSA had the largest metropolitan population of MSM in New Jersey at 105,269, or 79.4% of all MSM in the state and 26.5% of the 397,399 MSM in the MSA. Of the 2,396,110 adult men in the New Jersey part of New York-Newark-Jersey City, an estimated 4.4% were MSM. This was less than the percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA as a whole, which was 5.5% of adult men (397,399 out of 7,239,158).



Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Philadelphia-Camden-Wilmington Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Philadelphia-Camden-Wilmington MSA overlaps four states: Delaware, Maryland, New Jersey and Pennsylvania. The New Jersey portion of the MSA had 19,171 MSM, or 14.5% of all MSM in the state and 19.1% of the 100,293 MSM in the MSA. Of 483,025 adult men in the New Jersey part of Philadelphia-Camden-Wilmington, 4.0% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 4.6% of adult men (100,293 out of 2,189,761).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Trenton Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Trenton MSA had a population of 3,364 MSM, or 2.5% of all MSM in New Jersey. Of the 137,976 adult men in Trenton, an estimated 2.4% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Atlantic City-Hammonton Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Atlantic City-Hammonton MSA had a population of 2,135 MSM, or 1.6% of all MSM in New Jersey. Of the 101,114 adult men in Atlantic City-Hammonton, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Vineland-Bridgeton Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Vineland-Bridgeton MSA had a population of 1,201 MSM, or 0.9% of all MSM in New Jersey. Of the 61,895 adult men in Vineland-Bridgeton, an estimated 1.9% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Ocean City Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Ocean City MSA had a population of 794 MSM, or 0.6% of all MSM in New Jersey. Of the 37,909 adult men in Ocean City, an estimated 2.1% were MSM.

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.




Allentown-Bethlehem-Easton Metropolitan Statistical Area

The Allentown-Bethlehem-Easton MSA overlaps two states: New Jersey and Pennsylvania. The New Jersey portion of the MSA had 586 MSM, or 0.4% of all MSM in the state and 8.9% of the 6,577 MSM in the MSA. Of 39,933 adult men in the New Jersey part of Allentown-Bethlehem-Easton, 1.5% were MSM. This was less than the overall percentage of MSM among adult men in the MSA, which was 2.1% of adult men (6,577 out of 307,373).

Note: Range cutpoints for the map are based on the distribution of MSM among all counties in the United States.
